status_message: "I don't have the words to describe how it was, when you know that you could be dead in one or two hours, it made you sick, made you crazy,"  said Justin Sonder, the youngest of the witnesses at 90, who arrived at Auschwitz at the age of 17.  He told the court that after three or four months he was considered one of the "older" prisoners and feared most selection days, when SS men would look at rows of inmates, who were forced to stand in a line naked for up to four hours, and decide who was still fit to work and who should be killed.
link_name: Auschwitz  survivors tell former SS officer's trial  of killings

Hi all - just wanted to let you know that this page will now become the official page for The Irish Times on Facebook. Many thanks to Irish Times reader John Doyle who started this page and who kindly offered it to us for our official use. We look forward to keeping you updated and hearing your thoughts and feedback.

Comments which are NOT spam are being marked by some people here as spam. While we all have the right to disagree with the opinions of others, please have the courtesy not to mark as spam any comments that are expressed in a respectful manner just because you happen to disagree with them. GENUINE spam only to be marked as spam from now on, thank you.

Sorry for the long delay, I have been informed that the Irish Times hope to have the new official page up and running in the next few weeks, when the new page is up and running, we would ask that you drop this page from your favourites and add the new page to your 'likes'. Thank you. 

Please note that all spam and irrelevant posts will be removed, and repeat offenders will be reported to facebook. Thank you.
Ref : New Facebook page. Further details will be given when available.

Ladies and gentlemen, a new official page for the Irish Times is currently in the making. It is hoped that this page can gradually "close down" over the next few weeks, and you can transfer to the new page with relative ease. Thank you for you continued support.
Please note, this is a fan page for the Irish Times, it is not officially endorsed by the Irish Times. Thanks ;-)
